1 B. An officer or other person acting by the officer’s command
2 in the officer’s aid and assistance whose use of deadly force is
3 found during any pretrial hearing or proceeding to be unjustified
4 pursuant to this section may appeal such ruling to the Court of
5 Criminal Appeals within ten (10) days of the ruling. Priority shall
6 be given to appeals made pursuant to this subsection and an order
7 staying proceedings shall be entered pending the outcome of the
8 appeal. If an appeal is not brought within ten (10) days of the
9 ruling, the officer waives the right to immediate appeal of the
10 ruling but does not waive any right to assert the claim at trial or
11 upon direct appeal.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
